      "es": "",
      "en": "Serialize obj as a JSON formatted stream to fp (a .write()-supporting file-like object) using this Python-to-JSON conversion table. Note Unlike pickle and marshal, JSON is not a framed protocol, so trying to serialize multiple objects with repeated calls to dump() using the same fp will result in an invalid JSON file. Parameters: obj (object) – The Python object to be serialized. fp (file-like object) – The file-like object obj will be serialized to. The json module always produces str object..."
